# PR & Issue Templates
Always follow the official templates when submitting PRs or Issues to kubernetes-sigs/kubespray.
## Pull Request Template
Reference: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/kubespray/blob/master/.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md
Every PR must include:
**1. PR Kind** (uncomment exactly one):
```
/kind api-change /kind bug /kind cleanup /kind design /kind documentation /kind failing-test /kind feature /kind flake
```
**2. Required sections:**
- **What this PR does / why we need it**: Clear description of the change and motivation
- **Which issue(s) this PR fixes**: Use `Fixes #<issue>` to auto-close linked issues
- **Special notes for your reviewer**: Any context reviewers need
- **Does this PR introduce a user-facing change?**: Include a `release-note` block:
  ```release-note
  <description or NONE>
  ```
## Issue Templates
Reference: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/kubespray/tree/master/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE

Available templates:
- **bug-report.yaml** — for reporting bugs
- **enhancement.yaml** — for feature requests / enhancements
- **failing-test.yaml** — for CI/test failures

Use the appropriate template; do not file a blank issue when a template matches.
